Customer Experience & Product Satisfaction Analysis
Overview

This project focuses on analyzing customer satisfaction, product experience, and renewal behavior for a healthcare insurance service provider using survey-based Net Promoter Score (NPS) analytics. The objective was to identify the key factors influencing customer loyalty, dissatisfaction, and retention through data-driven insights and interactive dashboards.

Using Python, Power BI, and VBA, the analysis transformed raw customer feedback into actionable business recommendations that could support product improvement strategies, customer engagement initiatives, and service optimization efforts.

The project analyzed 231 customer survey responses and achieved an overall NPS score of +15, highlighting both strengths in customer trust and critical gaps in pricing perception, communication, and renewal experience.

Business Problem

Healthcare insurance providers often face challenges in balancing customer trust, pricing expectations, and long-term retention. While customers may appreciate the service quality during claims, dissatisfaction can grow due to:

Rising premium costs
Poor communication during renewals
Lack of perceived value among customers who never claim benefits
Long support wait times
Weak loyalty recognition for long-term customers

The objective of this project was to:

Understand what drives customer satisfaction and dissatisfaction
Identify high-risk customer segments
Analyze customer sentiment and renewal behavior
Recommend product and customer experience improvements
Build dashboards for business stakeholders to monitor satisfaction trends
